body:
@clintropolis thanks for the quick fix! It works in my local.

Looks that Travis is not being started because of [Slow booting linux builds issue in Travis](https://www.traviscistatus.com/).

I would vote for merging this PR without waiting for Travis because it's blocking people from building master.

@leventov looks nice! two small suggestions:
1. There is no hyperlink to `committer-instructions.md`, I think `CONTRIBUTING.md` should link to it.
2. I think the asset files should be organized into sub-folders (perhaps `TeamCity_images`, `IDE_images`), especially since there is no README.md in the folder so it's harder to sort things out.

> @michael-trelinski thank you for your contribution! Would you please write a proposal for this PR? Here is the link: https://github.com/apache/incubator-druid/issues/new/choose.

@jihoonson: Should I add this as a Feature/Change or a Proposal?  I can see merits for both.

Also, IntelliJ lied to me and the unit tests were broken, so I pushed another commit, which hopefully fixes it.

@jon-wei looking at the `Theta` sketch, can't it basically do everything `HLL` sketch can do?
Is the `HLL` sketch just faster than `Theta` sketch but covers less use cases?

Ie, is it correct to say `HLL` is a subset of `Theta` sketch in terms of features, but we include it cause its faster?
